DOCUMENTATION: Cloudflare + GCP Ingress SSL — Secure Setup Guide
================================================================================
Date: 2026-03-12
Domain: poker.vincentlam.xyz
Stack: User → Cloudflare (Proxy) → GCP Global LB (GKE Ingress) → Pods

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ARCHITECTURE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  User
   │  HTTPS
   ▼
Cloudflare (Orange Cloud — Proxy ON)
   │  HTTPS (Full Strict — validates GCP cert)
   ▼
GCP Global External Load Balancer
  IP: 35.244.226.243
  Ingress: poll-ingress (namespace: default)
  TLS cert: cert-manager + Let's Encrypt (secret: poker-tls)
   │
   ├── /api/polls  → poll-service:80  → pods on port 3001
   ├── /api/vote   → vote-service:80  → pods on port 3001
   └── /           → poker-planning-service:80 → pods on port 80

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CLOUDFLARE SETTINGS (Required)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

DNS Record:
  Type:    A
  Name:    poker.vincentlam.xyz
  Value:   35.244.226.243
  Proxy:   Proxied (Orange Cloud ON)  ← hides real IP, enables DDoS protection

SSL/TLS Settings:
  Mode:             Full (Strict)
                    ← Cloudflare validates GCP's TLS cert end-to-end
                    ← Do NOT use "Flexible" (insecure) or "Full" (no validation)

Edge Certificates:
  Always Use HTTPS: ON  ← enforces HTTP → HTTPS redirect (301)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
WHY FULL STRICT MODE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Cloudflare has 4 SSL modes:

  Off        → No encryption. Never use.
  Flexible   → Cloudflare↔GCP is HTTP. Insecure, cert not validated.
  Full       → Cloudflare↔GCP is HTTPS but cert not validated.
               Vulnerable to MITM between Cloudflare and GCP.
  Full Strict → Cloudflare↔GCP is HTTPS AND cert is validated.
               Requires a valid cert on GCP side. Most secure. USE THIS.

With cert-manager + Let's Encrypt, GCP has a valid cert → Full Strict works.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
WHY ORANGE CLOUD (PROXIED) MATTERS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

With orange cloud ON:
  - Real GCP IP (35.244.226.243) is hidden from public
  - DDoS protection active
  - Cloudflare WAF active
  - HTTP → HTTPS redirect enforced by Cloudflare

With grey cloud (DNS Only):
  - Real IP is publicly visible
  - No DDoS protection
  - No WAF
  - Only use temporarily for debugging or cert provisioning issues

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CERT-MANAGER + LET'S ENCRYPT
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Certificates are managed automatically by cert-manager in the cluster.

Check certificate status:
  kubectl get certificate poker-tls
  kubectl describe certificate poker-tls

Certificate details:
  Issuer:   letsencrypt-prod (ClusterIssuer)
  Secret:   poker-tls
  Valid:    90 days (auto-renewed by cert-manager before expiry)
  Renewal:  ~30 days before expiry

If cert renewal fails, check:
  kubectl get certificaterequest,order,challenge

WARNING: If Cloudflare is in Proxied mode during initial cert provisioning,
the Let's Encrypt HTTP-01 challenge WILL FAIL. To provision a new cert:
  1. Temporarily set Cloudflare to DNS Only (grey cloud)
  2. Wait for cert to become Ready (kubectl get certificate)
  3. Re-enable Proxied (orange cloud)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
GCP HEALTH CHECKS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

GCP health checkers probe pods directly (NEG mode) from these IP ranges:
  130.211.0.0/22
  35.191.0.0/16

Required firewall rule:
  Name:          allow-gcp-health-checks
  Direction:     INGRESS
  Protocol:      TCP (all ports)
  Source ranges: 130.211.0.0/22, 35.191.0.0/16
  Target:        (all instances)

Verify it exists:
  gcloud compute firewall-rules describe allow-gcp-health-checks \
    --project poker-planning-489721

BackendConfig health check settings:
  API services (poll, vote):   port 3001, path /
  Frontend (poker-planning):   port 80,   path /

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
GKE INGRESS REQUIREMENTS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The GKE ingress-gce controller requires BOTH:
  1. spec.ingressClassName: gce              (new-style)
  2. annotations:
       kubernetes.io/ingress.class: gce      (legacy — required for controller
                                              to add its finalizer and provision
                                              GCP load balancer resources)

Without the legacy annotation, the ingress-gce controller silently ignores
the Ingress and never provisions the GCP load balancer.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VERIFICATION COMMANDS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Check all backends are HEALTHY:
  kubectl get ingress poll-ingress -o jsonpath='{.metadata.annotations.ingress\.kubernetes\.io/backends}'

Test SSL directly on GCP LB (bypass Cloudflare):
  curl -sI --resolve poker.vincentlam.xyz:443:35.244.226.243 https://poker.vincentlam.xyz

Test HTTP redirect via Cloudflare:
  curl -sI http://poker.vincentlam.xyz
  # Expected: HTTP/1.1 301 Moved Permanently → https://poker.vincentlam.xyz/

Test full HTTPS via Cloudflare:
  curl -sI https://poker.vincentlam.xyz
  # Expected: HTTP/1.1 200 OK, Server: cloudflare

Check certificate:
  kubectl get certificate poker-tls
  # Expected: READY = True

