--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
TROUBLESHOOTING QUICK REFERENCE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Problem: Cloudflare Error 525 (SSL Handshake Failed)
  Cause:  GCP load balancer has no valid TLS cert, or ingress not provisioned
  Fix:    Check kubectl get certificate, check kubectl describe ingress for IP

Problem: GCP backends UNHEALTHY
  Cause:  Health check hitting wrong port, or BackendConfig not applied
  Fix:    Check BackendConfig port matches container port (3001 for API)
          Verify kubectl get backendconfig

Problem: Ingress has no IP after creation/recreation
  Cause:  Missing kubernetes.io/ingress.class: gce annotation
  Fix:    kubectl annotate ingress poll-ingress kubernetes.io/ingress.class=gce

Problem: Let's Encrypt cert not provisioning
  Cause:  Cloudflare Proxy intercepts HTTP-01 challenge
  Fix:    Temporarily set Cloudflare to DNS Only, wait for cert, re-enable proxy

Problem: New image not deployed after push
  Cause:  imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent caches old image on node
  Fix:    Use imagePullPolicy: Always + kubectl rollout restart

